  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anemia and preoperative iron deficit in cardiac surgery are associated by an increased volume&#xD;
      of transfusion and an increase in complications and/or mortality. Recent studies have shown&#xD;
      that EPO and iron administration the days preceding the operation results in a reduction of&#xD;
      perioperative transfusion for patients with preoperative anemia.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
